@SP

Thanks for the recommendation.

As you may have noticed, I tried to defend the editors on Wednesday, but couldn't keep up my good intentions today.

@James

I have no idea whether what you say is accurate, but even if it is, the wording of the clue doesn't preclude that they only sponsor the cars. It simply says it's a sponsor of (i.e. "involved in") the series.  

My Mets wear a patch bearing the name of their sponsoring hospital (the one that does complicated orthopedic surgery) on their uniforms.  I would say they're an MLB sponsor, even if they don't sponsor the whole league.  (Heaven knows, they're an apt choice to sponsor that team.)

@Tim
The part that bothers me is the "green" or "clean" appended to so-called renewable energy. It tends to elide the real environmental devastation these "green" energy sources can create: strip mines and slave labor to produce batteries for electric vehicles; destruction of ecosystems for hydroelectric power; the postapocalyptic nightmare that is nuclear energy.

Here's an idea: why don't we all just use less energy? Let's start with no new data centers.

